  "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/32971419/can-not-select-id-of-a-persian-value-from-the-microsoft-sql-server-in-android",
  "title" : "can not select Id of a Persian value from the Microsoft SQL server in Android",
  "body" : "<p>I have MSSQL DB, which is SQL_Latin1_General_CP1_CI_AS collation and filled out with some Persian values.\nThe type of the field stored in DB is String(nvarchar(50), null)\nI want to get the ID of this String, that is integer, so I open my connection and write this in my code:</p>\n<pre><code>ConnectionHelper connectionHelper = new ConnectionHelper();\nstatement2 = connectionHelper.getConnection().createStatement();\nsetType();\nResultSet resultSet = statement2.executeQuery(&quot;select Id from tblProductCategory where Name='&quot; + getType() + &quot;'&quot;);\n</code></pre>\n<p>But I couldn't, getType() returns a string in Persian from my GridView.</p>\n<p>After hours, I insert Latin String in my tblProductCategory and select its ID, and it worked correctly. My problem is with Persian Language.\nI searched and find that MSSQL server doesn't have utf-8, but nvarchar supports this.</p>\n<p>Any idea?</p>\n"
}